The paper proposes a new approach for learned DBMS components that is data-driven rather than workload-driven. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the database (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of machine learning models for query answering and cardinality estimation, which are common tasks in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data science (cs.DS). Finally, the paper also discusses the generalization of the proposed approach to unseen queries, which is a topic of interest in information retrieval (cs.IR).
